It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. It's the last room in the house that has only been minimally decorated.
Demolish the ugly electric fireplace and the furnace bed. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Custom order a wardrobe.
We usually start with a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
A few dead birds were found behind the chimney, their bodies completely dried up :(
Prepare for the plastering workers next week
Satisfying with the small niche next to it
Install the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing it yet 😅)
Ha ha, check out what we found behind the radiator!
Remember the cute little vent we added to prevent the chimney from getting damp
Sweep the chimney cap and chimney cover are both installed. The white-necked crows that like to nest in the chimney should be safer from now on 🪺
The plastering workers have finished their work. We will lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork padding has been laid, and we made a accessory for the vacuum cleaner using a roll of toilet paper to clean up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor has been prepared and is ready to start laying. Let's have a cup of tea and rest first.
Well, today's progress was a bit slow because, to seamlessly connect with the corridor (which is also being laid with flooring), we needed to cut around the door frame, which was quite tedious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me
Finally finished, but it's all messed up! Even worse, the instructions for assembling the new bed are terrible. Finally, I can sleep well tonight!
The corridor floor and baseboards are still not done. The renovation workers will come a month later, so we can only manage with what we have now, and the room is just bare plaster.
DIYed a bit in the evening, using a dovetail saw and chisel to cut part of the bottom of the door frame, so the floor can fit perfectly underneath.
The cork underlayment for the corridor is also laid
We also laid the corridor floor yesterday! Got up at 5 a.m. today to go to Heathrow Airport to collect the first package, then took a nap, and now finally can start installing the baseboards for the corridor. Wait for the glue to dry before filling the gaps.
